### Route Protection
Auth checks happen in layout components (client-side):
- `/writer/*` — `useSession()` hook redirects unauthenticated users to signin (all roles: admin, writer, drafter)
- `/settings/*` — checks `session.user.role === 'admin'`, redirects non-admins to writer
- **Publishing**: API routes check `canPublish(role)` before allowing `status: 'published'`; editor UI hides Publish button for drafters
This approach avoids Edge runtime limitations with Prisma.

